"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-athletics-2024-0711-1459429-mawdsley-ill-run-as-often-as-i-can-at-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Declan Whooley  RT\\u00c9 Sport Online Journalist  \\\"You have officially been selected\\\"  Five words that have been the motivating force behind Sharlene Mawdsley's determination to realise her dream as an Olympian.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Declan_Napier\", \"score\": 0.9407107480259344, \"rank\": 0.06302601740038262, \"text\": \"Declan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Declan_Napier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Declan_Napier\"}, {\"begin\": 197, \"end\": 205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999258762, \"rank\": 7.395538024537144e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Confirmation of her place in Paris came via an email from Athletics Ireland yesterday morning, previous heartache washed away by instant relief.\", \"from\": 208, \"to\": 352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 237, \"end\": 242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.155752270964535e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 266, \"end\": 283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Ireland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Athletics Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her on-track performances and silverware this season meant there was, in truth, little doubt over her selection, but the Tipperary native has scar tissue from her Tokyo ordeal.\", \"from\": 354, \"to\": 530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 517, \"end\": 522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9806452600761638, \"rank\": 0.019736735822766843, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having been part of the Irish 4x400m mixed relay that secured Olympic qualification,she was cut from the team at the expense of Cliodhna Manning, who got the better of her at the nationals.\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 556, \"end\": 561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9986759212674745, \"rank\": 0.0009280045104969179, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A crestfallen Mawdsley vowed immediately to do everything in her power to make the plane to Paris, with the first six months of 2024 testament to that as she soared from one high to another.\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 815, \"end\": 820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.155752270964535e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Until I got that email I did not believe I was going, maybe a bit of PTSD from not going three years ago,\\\" she told RT\\u00c9 Sport.\", \"from\": 915, \"to\": 1042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT\\u00c9_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9999999789533833, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9 Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT\\u00c9_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT\\u00c9_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I promised myself after 2021 that I would give it everything for the three years to try and qualify for Paris and if it did not work out at least I would never look back and say I did not try my best.\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.155752270964535e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I did and here I am going to the Olympics which is so exciting.\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wasn't leaving that unturned this year, because I did not want anyone to take my spot away.\\\"\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'We have two really strong relay teams' -Paris-bound Sharlene Mawdsley is targeting an Olympic medalpic.twitter.com/e6k3qKTJRp  While she had not considered herself superstitious, she was leaving nothing to chance.\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1626, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Newport native warned her mother not to book any flights - \\\"of course she did it behind my back anyways\\\" - and purposefully avoided talking to her coach Gary Ryan about his presence in Paris.\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1631, \"end\": 1638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newport_RFC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.674971861254924e-17, \"text\": \"Newport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newport_RFC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newport_RFC\"}, {\"begin\": 1784, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Ryan_(athlete)\", \"score\": 0.6116469187259833, \"rank\": 0.6349206349205021, \"text\": \"Gary Ryan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Ryan_(athlete)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Ryan_(athlete)\"}, {\"begin\": 1816, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.155752270964535e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even the scheduling of events is not something she has reeled off just yet, but that is likely to change.\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1929, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The calendar of events in the French capital will come under the microscope over the coming weeks with Mawdsley, Sophie Becker and Rhasidat Adeleke all potentially available for the mixed relay, women's relay and the individual 400m.\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 2164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1961, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9965275076443757, \"rank\": 0.0028605015097926474, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2044, \"end\": 2057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Becker\", \"score\": 0.9999944927823652, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sophie Becker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Becker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Becker\"}, {\"begin\": 2062, \"end\": 2078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhasidat_Adeleke\", \"score\": 0.9999999999349711, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rhasidat Adeleke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhasidat_Adeleke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhasidat_Adeleke\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adeleke was to the fore in the Bahamas as Ireland secured Olympic qualification in both the women's and mixed 4x400m, but what path she follows remains to be seen.\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2197, \"end\": 2204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"score\": 0.9999999998485691, \"rank\": 1.0202364356969203e-10, \"text\": \"Bahamas\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\"}, {\"begin\": 2208, \"end\": 2215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999795870335951, \"rank\": 2.0372329148674913e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletics schedule is bookended by the mixed relay and women's relay - the women's relay final on 10 August falls on Mawdsley's 26th birthday - so what that means for Adeleke in her quest for silverware in the individual event has been the subject of much discussion.\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2602, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Having run five times in six days at the European Championships in Rome to collect silver (women's relay) and gold in the mixed relay, Mawdsley's outlook is pretty straight forward.\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2671, \"end\": 2675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9324154437394766, \"rank\": 0.07228780407035917, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will go out on the track as many times as I can,\\\" she insists, \\\"either before my individual event or after.\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To be an Olympian means everything, and I am a big team player, I love the relays.\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2982, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2909, \"end\": 2917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999258762, \"rank\": 7.395538024537144e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So I do not see why I would not do it.\\\"\", \"from\": 2983, \"to\": 3022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With Ireland now firmly established as a relay force, how would she feel if Adeleke decided to skip an event to boost her own chances of success in a tight schedule?\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3189, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3029, \"end\": 3036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999795870335951, \"rank\": 2.0372329148674913e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think Rhasidat has to make the decision that's best for her.\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3254, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I would have no hard feelings at all.\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think I am going to be challenging for a gold medal, not this year anyway, so I am not in that position to be able to say what I would do.\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I respect her decision regardless of what she does, of course we would absolutely love to have her on the team, that's no secret, but whatever she does is what's best for her.\\\"\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mawdsley is looking to bring a little more of her relay fight to the individual party next month, with Rome a reminder of her capabilities with the bit between her teeth.\", \"from\": 3631, \"to\": 3801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3734, \"end\": 3738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9324154437394766, \"rank\": 0.07228780407035917, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With gold in the bag from the mixed relay,Mawdsley ran a superb anchor leg (49.76)to power Ireland into the women's final as heat winners just a day afterher exploits in the 400m individual final (51.59).\", \"from\": 3803, \"to\": 4007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3894, \"end\": 3901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999795870335951, \"rank\": 2.0372329148674913e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the final she ran a blistering leg (49.84) and looked capable of overtaking winner Femke Bol before the Netherlands athlete kept her cool on the home stretch.\", \"from\": 4009, \"to\": 4170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4095, \"end\": 4104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Femke Bol\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Femke_Bol\"}, {\"begin\": 4116, \"end\": 4127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.7328147348416586, \"rank\": 0.3643488572304014, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That heat of the women's relay, I was like cruising along and it was 49.\", \"from\": 4172, \"to\": 4245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was like, 'if only I could do that in my individual'.\", \"from\": 4246, \"to\": 4301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A rolling start makes your start faster automatically, but I just seem to have that extra edge when I go to a relay.\", \"from\": 4303, \"to\": 4420, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That little hunger, I see the finish line a lot sooner than in the individual.\\\"\", \"from\": 4421, \"to\": 4500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Can she bring that steely determination into individual?\", \"from\": 4502, \"to\": 4558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's what we have been working on the past few weeks, the past few months.\", \"from\": 4560, \"to\": 4637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are some races where I am coming out, 'yes, I did that', and other races where I am like, 'ooops, I forgot to do that today'.\", \"from\": 4638, \"to\": 4769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's exciting that there are always things to improve on.\\\"\", \"from\": 4770, \"to\": 4828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Next week she departs on a camp, the last gruelling hard block of training before Paris.\", \"from\": 4830, \"to\": 4918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4912, \"end\": 4917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.155752270964535e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With no races between now and then, everything will be put into these few weeks to sharpen up before competing on the biggest stage.\", \"from\": 4919, \"to\": 5051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am going in knowing that I am going to relish every moment, but I do know that I am going to be bringing my A game,\\\" she says.\", \"from\": 5053, \"to\": 5182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will be going in enjoying it but still I am going to be competitive.\", \"from\": 5184, \"to\": 5255, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not going in to make up the numbers.\", \"from\": 5256, \"to\": 5297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a championships so anything can really happen.\", \"from\": 5299, \"to\": 5351, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I will have the relay at the start to hopefully calm my nerves, but I want to be going in running 50.5 (individual), I think that's kind of in and around where I am at so I would be disappointed to not show my capabilities that I am showing in training, in the competition.\", \"from\": 5352, \"to\": 5625, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is an Olympic Games at the end of the day, things will happen but I think the excitement of it all is really going to push me on.\\\"\", \"from\": 5627, \"to\": 5761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 5763, \"to\": 5774, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 5775, \"to\": 5865, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5800, \"end\": 5823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851270567, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 5825, \"end\": 5832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999795870335951, \"rank\": 2.0372329148674913e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.\", \"from\": 5866, \"to\": 5932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5866, \"end\": 5869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9835396432123026, \"rank\": 0.013767790549921992, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\", \"from\": 5934, \"to\": 5966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5953, \"end\": 5958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999853824819807, \"rank\": 9.381441242965906e-06, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}]}]}"